SKSurface.Create started to return null in 1.59.1, but worked fine in 1.57.1

```csharp
int w = 1968;
int h = 1412;
double dpi = 2.5;

WriteableBitmap bmp = new WriteableBitmap(w, h, dpi, dpi, PixelFormats.Pbgra32, null);
bmp.Lock();

using (var surface = SKSurface.Create(
              width: w,
              height: h,
              colorType: SKColorType.Bgra8888,
              alphaType: SKAlphaType.Premul,
              pixels: bmp.BackBuffer,
              rowBytes: w * 4))
            {
                SKCanvas canvas = surface.Canvas;   //surface is null at this point
            }

bmp.Unlock();
```
